Morise teleports in, and removes the air from several muns lungs. While they're waiting for them to die, they start to dissect one that's already dead.

The results are interesting, and they catalogue the body parts on display in the shelves. The rest are dead now, and blood soaks the room. They move onto the next mun, ignoring the cries of one who's still alive. They're irritated now, and shut them up with an air spear through the head.

There. Silence. Perfect. They continue their work, splattering blood and crushing bones and plucking out parts. Theres a pile of bodies in one corner, and parts litter the desks and tables and shelves.

They're idly playing a game of air ping pong with an eyeball when the recent escapes come to mind, so they dissect the rest of the third mun and start tearing the fourth apart. That's satisfying, and they grin to themself.
When they're done with that body, it's essentially shredded, so they incinerate it and spread the rest out in an orderly line. Femurs. They need more femurs. They get to work.

"My, *my*, Morise.. *Quite* the dramatic looser, aren't you?" Illuvies coos, placing a single finger to his bottom lip as his gaze lingers around the room. He lets out a satisfied sigh Lingering feelings of pure terror, despise, hatred.. It's all *delicious.*

"Not a loser. It's just calming." They say, digging their fingers into what remains of a torso. "You're the one who's making it weird. I'm just returning these muns to the natural state of not being. Maybe their atoms can contribute to something useful, like a Plasma, next time."

"You're *very* much a loser, my dear," he hums, walking forward. He completely ignores the rest of her words. "It seems the Kujo's have outsmarted you.. *twice*, might I add. *Quite* the embarrassment, don'tcha think?"
He casually says, pulling out a long intestine from one of the mutilated corpses. "Those two must be feeling plenty proud of themselves."
".....Whatever you think." They snap off some ribs. "I don't care any longer." They raise their eyebrows at the intestine. "Would you like to join these?"

"Darling, couldn't lay a hand on me if you tried," he chuckles casually, dropping the intestine he was holding to the ground, watching it splat down with a wet plop. "You're loosing this war, Morise."
"So you think." They sigh. "So you think." They lift the ribs into the air and start arranging them by size. Noticeably, they also coil the intestine back up. "If you say so."

"I do. And I will continue to unless you turn the tides around Though at this point, I doubt that's possible."
He places his foot on a corpses head, placing his cheek in his face and sighing. "Oh to be a mun.. So small," he crushes the skull under his foot, "..So weak. Powerless, even, unless you let them be powerful."

"Illuvies, I must say. You have very little faith in me. I can make people explode with a wave of my hand. I'm handicapping myself to see how they react - if they're close to winning, I can simply use my full abilities."

"Then why haven't you?"
He picks up a bloody piece of skull, examining it carefully. "You're capable of *so much more* than you allow, yet when this whole thing began, the only reason you weren't sliced in the throat is because dear Riri tried to convince you to not be an evil dictator."

"I'm a sideliner right now. I'll join the fray with my power when I've decided I have enough information. Right now I don't have enough. Also, slicing me in the throat is hardly enough to kill me. You know how Plasma work."

"You know what I mean, darling. Would you like me to go into more specifics? Mutilated," he steps in a blown-open corpses chest, "Tore through," he kicks a stomach out of it, "Completely and totally dismembered." He finishes off by stepping onto the stomach, crushing it. "What information could you possibly need? I, for one, am *absolutely* ready for a bloodbath."

They raise an eyebrow. "Aren't you just soooooo smart." They say dryly. "Can you please stop damaging those organs? They're useful." They lift their hand and the bodies explode open. "Better. You can have the muscles and stuff."

"Muscles arent as fun to toy with. Organs you can *smash* through with a foot. Muscles.. Are like stepping on pool noodles," he sticks his tongue out at the thought. "And, I *am,* Morise. Remember my ranking."
"I still outrank you, smart boy." Morise represents the council. "And yeah, I guess. You can have these ribs." They chuck them over.

He catches one, using the momentum to spin around and shoot it right back at Morise, whizzing right passed their ear and sticking into the wall. "You may represent them, but you do not outrank me by light years, my dear. If I ran this war, it'd be"
He pauses, thinking for a moment.
"..Well, it'd go on for years. I would *never* miss the opportunity to lengthen out chaos. If I ran this war, and *wanted* it to end, I would simply *end it.* You are pointlessly collecting information that will never be useful again and *that's* if you even manage to overcome these silly rebellions."
They catch the bone before it hits the wall. "Its for the archives. I like to study things. So let me indulge myself for once, wouldn't you?"

She looks down, clenching her hands on her knees. "..*Forcefully.* I saw them a few times after that, but.. That was all, I suppose. I wonder where they all went; not that I'm sad that they're gone."

"I am the Plasma of... sleep, or dreams, or something."

The metal bracelet Morise put on him was on the wrist his broken hand was on, making it harder to tend to.

"...Mm. Not sure how you'd get that off,"
She murmurs, poking at the device.
"I'm not sure how hard it would be to bully Morise into telling me, but I don't particularly want to fuck around and find out *quite* yet."

"Hmm.."
She hands off the bandage to a vine, allowing it to carefully continue her work. Another vine appears and pokes at the device, attempting to slip under her own.

She cocks her head.
"Careful with that- Morise's shit can be a little murder-y, in my experience."

"I'm willing to take the risk if it means we're one step closer to getting out of here."
The vine manages to slip under, wrapping itself around the bracelet and tugging at it.

She carefully rests a hand on Seiko's arm.
*"Careful.* Like I said, they have a nasty habit of making things that will hurt or kill you."

"Well what else am I supposed to do!? I got myself and my son *whom I just met* stuck in- in this *miniature hell!* I have no clue how we're going to get out a second time, I'm not even sure what these things *do,* and we're fighting a being who can CUT OFF OUR AIR! I don't believe you realize how grave this situation is And I don't even know your name!"
Polaris looks to the side guiltily, staying quiet throughout the rant. Part of the reason any of this is happening is because *he* left in the first place. *Fuck.*

She paps her other hand onto her head and looks her in the eye.
"Shh. I realize."

"..."
Her brows furrow, small tears poking at her eyes as she shoves her face in her hands Everything's too *much.* She's getting overwhelmed. Polaris places his uninjured hand (well.. less injured than his completely mutilated hand) on her back, not sure how to comfort her.

Somnus gives her an awkward pat, unsure of how to handle this. 
"Do you... want a hug? Or something?"
She shoves her fist into her knees, sniffling as she nods.
Honestly, she doesn't know what else to do- this is probably her best bet. She scoots closer, trying to pull Seiko in as gently as possible.
She lets herself be pulled, wrapping her arms around the Plasma and holding her tight as she cries into her chest. Polaris looks up at Somnus awkwardly, blinking.
She blinks back at him, awkwardly patting Seiko. People just *do* this? Regularly? Weird.

"'M gonna see if I can warp out," Polaris mumbles out groggily. It's the first idea he has. 
Seiko lets go of the Plasma after a few moments, backing up and wiping her tears with her wrist, sniffling. "Th-Thank you.."

"Mhm."
She nods down at her and gives her a quick pat on the head before swivelling her head back over to Polaris.
"That's dumb. Don't do that."
"'S not dumb. What else can I do?"
"Rest, and scheme. I am not stronger than Morise, so I can't guarantee I'll be able to stop them if they decide they're in a child bullying mood."
"My scheme is that I'm going to warp out of here," he hums, pushing himself off the wall and standing up lazily.

"Bad scheme. Shut up."
She grabs his arm.
"Morise wouldn't make it that easy for you unless they had some shit planned."
He tugs his arm. "Somnus, I don't think you realize but I'm fighting the a strong panic attack right now. I want to get the fuck *out of here.* **Let me warp out of here.**"
*"You will die, or be badly injured.* Sit down."

Somnus Looks At Him.

"I *won't.*"

She Does Not Stop Looking.

He Looks Away. "I'm going to warp out of here," he tugs his arm again. "*Let me warp out of here.*"

"Don't be a dickhead. Sleep."
*What are you doing?* He stumbles a bit, but tugs his arm away harder. "*Stop.* Let me try. I'll just warp you with me," he threatens.

*"Sleep."*
She doesn't want to overdo it and make him pass out immediately- he might hit his head- but it seems like he's not planning on just laying down.
"Can you catch him? I'm gonna do something."

Seiko nods, her vines sprouting from her back quickly.
Polaris sees the vines, hears Somnus, and panics. In his panic, warps to the lake.

*"Shit-"*
She vanishes alongside him.

"...Hide the first aid,"
She mumbles as she retreats into the ducts.

"O-Oh.."

"I am *aware* that that's the experimentation table." They say, taking a look over the scratches over its surface. "I need to fix it up." They start working out the bloodstains.

*The experiment table!?*
"Why not lay him against a wall? Or bring him here, to this room? Why leave him on the experiment table?"
She is Concerned.
"Because it's the most convenient area to put him. The floor is dirty, he'll fall over if I put him against the wall, and there are cells here." They say, exasperated.

"I mean bring him to *me.* In the *cell that I'm in.*"
She resists the urge to roll her eyes Every passing second makes her more and more angry at this.. *asshole.*

"....That's just where I teleported to. And you're free to go anywhere that's not outside the Plasma Zone." They finished cleaning out the bloodstains, pick Polaris up, then drop him on the floor with a blank expression. "Are you happy now?"

"Of course I'm not happy! You just dropped my son on the floor like a pencil off a desk!"
Some vines go and carefully pick up Polaris, bringing him behind her shield of vines and laying him against the wall. *Vile creature.*
They smile to themself. "I'll see you around." They ignore the thought and open the door and walk out. They're going to *finish* their shower, thank you very much.

Somnus tumbles back out of the vent.
"What the *fuck* did I say?"

"My stupid idiot son!"

She turns to Somnus. "Your what? I know you said something about.. about representing dreams? Were you about to make him fall asleep?"

She nods.
"I didn't want him to hit his head, or anything- I should've just knocked him out."

"Mmmmmmm.."

"What part of this is your fault? *You* weren't the one who hurt him."
"I should've protected him! Or I should've just.. just stayed here! Not escaped!"
"It wasn't malicious, so it's kinda... unproductive to worry about it, I think. There are other people that would like to cause problems on *purpose,* they seem like the ones be concerned over."

"I suppose.."

"Morise said that we could travel anywhere, as long as it's in the Plasma zone. We should bring my son to one of those rooms. The nice ones, with the beds."

"Well.."

"..."
